				\begin{document}$$p({\mathrm{correct}}_{1})=p(\mathrm{S2}) \: {\mathrm{HR}}_{1} + p(\mathrm{S1}) \: (1-{\mathrm{FAR}}_{1})$$\end{document}p(correct1)=p(S2)HR1+p(S1)(1-FAR1)where HR1 = type 1 hit rate = p(response = “S2” | stimulus = S2) and FAR1 = type 1 false alarm rate = p(response = “S2” | stimulus = S1). The value of c1 that maximizes type 1 accuracy is given by2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
